<TITLE> 2 killed in gun battle with Kushtia police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, August 2 (bdnews24.com)  Two armed men were killed in an exchange of gunfire with police in Mirpur Upazila, Kushtia, on Sunday. Mirpur police assistant superintendent Alamgir Hossain said police had gone to Bil Amla village at around 3:45am acting on a tip-off that a gang of criminals had arranged a meeting there on the bank of the river Sagarkhali Mirpur. Sensing their presence the gang opened fire at the police and the police shot back, said Hossain. Two were killed in the crossfire. The dead men were identified as Jahangir Hossain, 30, and Yarul Islam, 28, of Kholishakundi village in Daulatpur Upazila. "There were several murder, kidnapping and hijacking cases against the two and they had been hiding out for a long time," said Sheikh Anwar Hossain, officer-in-charge of Mirpur Police Station. Police said they recovered a pistol, a shutter gun, nine rounds of bullets, three knives and bullet casings from the spot. The bodies were sent to Kushtia General Hospital morgue. bdnews
